	<title>Linear Equations with no Solutions</title>
	<caption>Linear Equations with no Solutions</caption>
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>If a system of linear equations has no solution, then the solution hyperplanes of its equations have no point in common.</para>
			
			<para><img src="ims/ThreeEqnsR2Overdetermined.gif"/></para>
			
			<para>There is exactly one way in which the RREF of the system indicates that there is no solution: The RREF contains a leading <latex>1</latex> in its augmented part.</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
\begin{array}{ccccccccccccccc|c}
0 & \cdots & 0 & 1 & * & \cdots & * & 0 & * & \cdots & * & 0 & * & \cdots & * & 0 \\
0 & \cdots & 0 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 0 & 1 & * & \cdots & * & 0 & * & \cdots & * & 0 \\
0 & \cdots & 0 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 0 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 0 & 1 & * & \cdots & * & 0 \\
\vdots &   &   & \vdots & &     &   & \vdots & &     &   & \vdots & &     & \vdots & \vdots \\
\vdots &   &   & \vdots & &     &   & \vdots & &     &   & \vdots & &     & \vdots & \vdots \\
0 & \cdots & 0 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 0 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 0 & 0 & * & ***    & * & 0 \\
{\color{red}0} & {\color{red}\dots} & {\color{red}0} & {\color{red}0} & {\color{red}0} & {\color{red}\dots} & {\color{red}0} & {\color{red}0} & {\color{red}0} & {\color{red}\dots} & {\color{red}0} & {\color{red}0} & {\color{red}0} & {\color{red}\dots} & {\color{red}0} & {\color{red}1} \\
0 & \cdots & 0 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 0 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 0 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 0 & 0 \\
\end{array}
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			
			<para>Why does the above system have no solution? â€“ To see this we only need to recall that a row with a leading <latex>1</latex> in its augmented part corresponds to an equation in the reduced system of the form:</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
\begin{array}{cccccccccc}
\colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x_1} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x_2} & + & \cdots & \cdots & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x_n} & = & {\color{red}1} \\
\end{array}
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			
			<para>The left hand side is always <latex>0</latex>, while the right hand side is <latex>1</latex>. So this particular equation has no solution. Hence the entire system has no simultaneous solutions. </para>
		</statement>
	</showme>
</showme.pack>